*Super Eagles Defender Calvin Bassey debuts for Ajax. The 2022 Johan Cruyff Shield, Featuring Ajax Amsterdam, winners of the 2021/ 2022 Eredivisie League and 2021/2022 KNVB Cup winners PSV Eindhoven, will be live on Saturday 30th July 2022 at 7pm Nigerian time on Talent Sports channel, Nigeria’s leading independent Sports channel. The Dutch Super Cup, which signals the start of the 2022/2023 Dutch football season, will be available on Talent Sports on AVO TV free, affording football lovers across Africa the opportunity to watch one of world football’s greatest rivalries. For Nigerians, there is more at stake as Super Eagles defender Calvin Bassey is confirmed to start for Ajax Amsterdam after his protracted work permit debacle. Speaking to a cross section of Journalists, chief executive officer of Talent Sport and Entertainment, owners of Talent Sports channel, Tolu Badejo reaffirmed the broadcasters commitment to bringing world-class football content to viewers in Africa for free. “We are excited to be bringing the Dutch Cup Live to our viewers for free and can assure the general public that we will reveal our broader plans for the 2022/2023 football season soon,” said Badejo. The defending champions of the Johan Cruyff Shield are PSV. PSV are also the most successful team in the trophy’s history, having won it 12 times, three times more than Ajax (9 wins) who have the unwanted record of losing in the Johan Cruyff Shield the most number of times – nine times, two times more than PSV (7). 